From: Cline (audit B2) <audit@ask>
Date: Tue, 05 May 2026 10:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] auto_bridge: gate L2FLOW netlink inbound on CAP_NET_ADMIN

Audit finding auto_bridge AB-02 (plans/audit/AUDIT-auto_bridge.md).

abm_nl_rcv_msg() is the kernel-side handler for the NETLINK_L2FLOW
socket created at auto_bridge.c:621. The L2FLOW_MSG_ENTRY message
type triggers abm_l2flow_msg_handle() which programs L2 flow entries
into the bridge fast-path. L2 flow entries control which frames bypass
the Linux bridge stack via FMan offload — i.e., this is a data-plane
reconfiguration surface.

There is no per-protocol capability wiring for NETLINK_L2FLOW, so any
process able to socket(AF_NETLINK, SOCK_RAW, NETLINK_L2FLOW) can call
in. netlink_capable(skb, CAP_NET_ADMIN) is the correct gate — it uses
the SENDER's credentials, which matters because abm_nl_rcv_msg is
invoked from netlink_rcv_skb deferred dispatch.

The handler returns -EPERM on deny; netlink_rcv_skb propagates the
error back to userspace via netlink_ack as NLMSG_ERROR with err.error
= -EPERM, which is the documented contract for netlink command
handlers (see Documentation/networking/netlink-spec.rst).

Audit reference: plans/audit/AUDIT-auto_bridge.md AB-02
Signed-off-by: Cline <audit@ask>
---
diff --git a/auto_bridge/auto_bridge.c b/auto_bridge/auto_bridge.c
--- a/auto_bridge/auto_bridge.c
+++ b/auto_bridge/auto_bridge.c
@@ -491,6 +491,17 @@ static int abm_nl_rcv_msg(struct sk_buff *skb, struct nlmsghdr *nlh ,struct netl
 struct l2flow_msg *l2flow_msg;
 struct nlattr *tb[L2FLOWA_MAX + 1];
 
+/* B2/AB-02: L2FLOW_MSG_ENTRY programs the bridge fast-path
+ * (frames bypass the Linux bridge stack via FMan offload).
+ * NETLINK_L2FLOW has no per-protocol capability wiring, so the
+ * handler is reachable by any task that can open a NETLINK_RAW
+ * socket. netlink_capable() consults the sender's creds (not
+ * current task) — required because we are in the deferred
+ * netlink_rcv_skb dispatch path. -EPERM is propagated back to
+ * userspace as NLMSG_ERROR by netlink_rcv_skb. */
+if (!netlink_capable(skb, CAP_NET_ADMIN))
+return -EPERM;
+
 type = nlh->nlmsg_type;
 
 if(type >= L2FLOW_MSG_MAX){